## Contract Type Drives Churn
Month-to-month customers have highest churn. Customers without long-term contracts are significantly more likely to leave.

## Low Tenure = High Risk
New customers churn more. Customers in their first year are at the highest risk of churn.

## High Charges = Higher Churn
From monthly charges chart, customers who churn often pay more. Customers with higher monthly charges are more likely to 
churn, possibly due to perceived cost vs value.

## Certain services = Higher Churn
Customers using Fiber optic internet service are at a higher risk of churn, suggesting service dissatisfaction.

## Payment Method Patterns
Some payment types churn more, in this case it would be electronic check. Payment method influences churn behavior, 
indicating possible friction in billing experience.

